The paper presents an algorithm for computing a cylindrical algebraic decomposition of a semialgebraic set, which is a topic in computational geometry and computational algebraic geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) are the most likely sub-categories. The algorithm also involves projection sets and cell decomposition, which are topics in computational topology and computational algebraic topology, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the algorithm has potential applications in control theory and robotics, which fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
